Resolution Description: The Department of Sanitation investigated this complaint and found no condition at the location.
The Department of Buildings investigated this complaint and determined that no further action was necessary.
The Department of Consumer Affairs inspected the business you named in your Service Request. To check results, call 311 with your Service Request Number and ask for Service Request Status - DCA.
The Police Department responded to the complaint and with the information available observed no evidence of the violation at that time.

The Department of Consumer Affairs has received your report. This request is under investigation. The Department of Consumer Affairs will work with other relevant City agencies and take enforcement action, as necessary.

The Taxi and Limousine Commission will send a confirmation letter in 14 days to confirm your complaint details. At the hearing you may be required to provide information regarding this complaint. Please note your Service Request number for future reference.
